An analysis is the largest reusable NEMS component. It excludes data loading,
initial model specification, and plotting. Analyses do two things repeatedly:
1) Run a FitSpaceMapping that creates a projector and unprojector.
You may use this to fit only a single module's parameters at a time,
run different fitters on each module, or select random parameter subsets.
2) Runs a Segmentor to pick the part of the data that you want to fit on.
You may use this to jacknife the data, or select only data matching specific
It is common to iterate many times and use various fitters, projectors, and
segmentors to accomplish some arbitrarily complex fitting task. It is also
common to manage multiple modelspecs, such as one for each jackknife of
the data, or a swarm of modelspecs that sample from the Bayesian posterior.
Please make analyses pure functions with no side effects.
